SIMPLE: insectivora
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insectivora
<hw>In`sec*tiv"o*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from L. <ets>insectum</ets> an insect + <ets>vorare</ets> to
devour.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An order of mammals
which feed principally upon insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ They are mostly of small size, and their molar teeth
have sharp cusps. Most of the species burrow in the earth, and many of
those of cold climates hibernate in winter. The order includes the
moles, shrews, hedgehogs, tanrecs, and allied animals, also the
colugo.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A division of the <ord>Chiroptera</ord>, including
the common or insect-eating bats.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insectivore</ent>⟦br⟧
